        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "chore(codex): mirror full app-server TypeScript protocol",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- mirror the complete experimental Codex app-server TypeScript protocol instead of retaining only a curated subset\n- make protocol drift checks compare the exact generated tree, including missing, changed, and stale files\n- verify the checked-out Codex Cargo workspace version matches the pinned `@openai/codex` package version\n- keep the vendored generated sources formatted and typechecked while excluding immutable upstream output from project lint rules\n\nThe previous sync/check path discarded most generated TypeScript and relied on selected semantic snippets, so new upstream protocol surfaces could arrive without a corresponding OpenClaw type mirror or drift failure. This establishes the generated tree as the canonical vendored surface. Replacing handwritten runtime adapters with generated types is intentionally out of scope.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/codex-app-server-protocol-source.test.ts` — 15 tests passed\n- `OPENCLAW_CODEX_REPO=<Codex rust-v0.139.0 checkout> pnpm codex-app-server:protocol:check` — exact 614-file mirror passed\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p extensions/codex/tsconfig.json --pretty false` — passed\n- `pnpm build` — passed\n- `pnpm check:changed` — all relevant lanes passed except extension test typechecking; four pre-existing Slack test errors reproduced on pristine `origin/main` at `extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts`\n- final autoreview — clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nRemote proof ran on Azure Crabbox `cbx_b39e75c049b7`; the lease was stopped after validation.\n\n## Risk\n\nThe main risk is the size of the generated diff and accidental generator/source mismatch. Exact source-version validation, byte-for-byte tree comparison, build/typecheck proof, and generated-output tests constrain that risk. There are no runtime, config, migration, or user-visible behavior changes in this PR.\n",
